This paper deals with algorithmic mechanism design for combinatorial auctions, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of game theory (cs.GT), data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computational economics (cs.EC). The paper specifically focuses on submodular bidders, which is a type of valuation function commonly studied in the algorithmic mechanism design literature. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.GT and cs.DS, followed by cs.AI, cs.EC, and cs.CC.
